# TUC–Mempool Consensus Protocol v1.3 (Deterministic DAG + Cryptographically Bound Timestamp Layer)

---

## 0. General Definition

TUC (Temporal Universal Consensus) is a distributed consensus protocol based on a **mempool structured as a DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph)**.

The system replaces physical time as a source of consensus, strictly separating two layers:

- **TUC-Time** → deterministic order derived from the DAG  
- **TUC-Timestamp** → external layer of temporal observability, cryptographically verifiable  

The system is fully deterministic at its core.

